{"by":"johnlbevan2","id":47776448,"kids":[47777250,47777236],"parent":47767928,"text":"Assuming I&#x27;ve understood correctly...<p>Checking the listed impacted web hooks I noticed that no repo&#x27;s listed twice, even though some have multiple hooks defined... That makes me think the report may have a bug.<p>Also, many of the listed hooks show as `This hook has never been triggered`; which if correct means it wouldn&#x27;t have had an issue as the compromised payload&#x27;s never been sent to it.<p>I&#x27;ll write a powershell script (well, AI will write it and then I&#x27;ll tweak) to help check which webhooks have been called in this time window (or at least, say they were most recently triggered after the issue first began) to help get a more accurate report of what&#x27;s concerning.  If that proves useful, I&#x27;ll share here.","time":1776243549,"type":"comment"}